# SBI Test Data Platform - Directory Structure

```
sbi-test-platform/
├── src/
│   ├── app/
│   │   └── page.jsx                 # Main entry point
│   ├── components/
│   │   ├── layout/
│   │   │   ├── Navbar.jsx          # Navigation bar component
│   │   │   ├── Sidebar.jsx         # Sidebar component
│   │   │   └── Footer.jsx          # Footer component
│   │   ├── pages/
│   │   │   ├── WelcomePage.jsx     # Landing page
│   │   │   ├── LoginPage.jsx       # Login page
│   │   │   ├── RegisterPage.jsx    # Registration page
│   │   │   └── Dashboard.jsx       # Main dashboard
│   │   ├── services/
│   │   │   ├── CIFService.jsx      # CIF creation service
│   │   │   ├── CCODService.jsx     # CCOD account service
│   │   │   └── DepositService.jsx  # Deposit service
│   │   ├── ui/
│   │   │   ├── StatsCard.jsx       # Statistics card component
│   │   │   ├── ProfileCard.jsx     # Profile information card
│   │   │   └── LoadingSpinner.jsx  # Loading component
│   │   └── shared/
│   │       └── ComingSoon.jsx      # Coming soon placeholder
│   ├── styles/
│   │   └── styles.js               # All inline styles
│   ├── utils/
│   │   ├── api.js                  # API utility functions
│   │   └── helpers.js              # Helper functions
│   └── constants/
│       └── config.js               # Configuration constants
├── public/
├── package.json
└── README.md
```

## File Contents

### 1. `/src/app/page.jsx`
Main application orchestrator that manages state and routing.

### 2. `/src/components/layout/Navbar.jsx`
Navigation bar for the welcome page with logo and authentication buttons.

### 3. `/src/components/layout/Sidebar.jsx`
Dashboard sidebar with navigation menu for different services.

### 4. `/src/components/layout/Footer.jsx`
Footer component for the welcome page.

### 5. `/src/components/pages/WelcomePage.jsx`
Landing page with hero section and feature cards.

### 6. `/src/components/pages/LoginPage.jsx`
Login page with authentication form.

### 7. `/src/components/pages/RegisterPage.jsx`
Registration page with user signup form.

### 8. `/src/components/pages/Dashboard.jsx`
Main dashboard container with navigation and service routing.

### 9. `/src/components/services/CIFService.jsx`
CIF creation form and results display.

### 10. `/src/components/services/CCODService.jsx`
CCOD account creation service (coming soon).

### 11. `/src/components/services/DepositService.jsx`
Deposit account creation service (coming soon).

### 12. `/src/components/ui/StatsCard.jsx`
Reusable statistics card component.

### 13. `/src/components/ui/ProfileCard.jsx`
User profile information card.

### 14. `/src/components/ui/LoadingSpinner.jsx`
Loading spinner component.

### 15. `/src/components/shared/ComingSoon.jsx`
Reusable coming soon placeholder.

### 16. `/src/styles/styles.js`
All inline styles exported as a single object.

### 17. `/src/utils/api.js`
API utility functions for fetch requests.

### 18. `/src/utils/helpers.js`
Helper functions like CSV download.

### 19. `/src/constants/config.js`
Configuration constants (API URL, regions, etc.).

## Benefits of This Structure

1. **Separation of Concerns**: Each component has a single responsibility
2. **Reusability**: UI components can be reused across different pages
3. **Maintainability**: Easy to locate and update specific functionality
4. **Scalability**: Easy to add new services or pages
5. **Organization**: Logical grouping by feature and function
6. **Testing**: Each component can be tested independently
7. **Collaboration**: Multiple developers can work on different components

## Next Steps

1. Create the directory structure as shown
2. Split the monolithic component into individual files
3. Export components from each file
4. Import and compose them in the main page.jsx
5. Keep all variable names and logic exactly the same
6. Maintain the same functionality while improving organization
